<section class="page-header shell">
  <p class="eyebrow">Evidence protocol // revision 0.1</p>
  <h1>Methodology</h1>
  <p>The Threshold is designed to show uncertainty rather than flatten it.</p>
</section>
<section class="section shell section--tight prose-grid">
  <article class="prose-card">
    <h2>Evidence classes</h2>
    <dl class="definition-list">
      <div><dt>Confirmed</dt><dd>Supported by direct or authoritative evidence.</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Reported</dt><dd>Published by a reliable outlet but not independently confirmed by the archive.</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Interpretation</dt><dd>Reasoned analysis that is visibly separated from the underlying facts.</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Signal</dt><dd>An action that may matter but has no confirmed meaning.</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Rumor</dt><dd>Informal or unverifiable discussion retained only when editorially relevant.</dd></div>
    </dl>
  </article>
  <article class="prose-card">
    <h2>Source hierarchy</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Direct statements, official uploads, and original records.</li>
      <li>Authoritative trade reporting and structured data sources.</li>
      <li>Secondary reporting with a traceable evidentiary chain.</li>
      <li>Community material used as a lead, not automatic confirmation.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>Multiple articles repeating one report count as one evidentiary chain.</p>
  </article>
  <article class="prose-card">
    <h2>Corrections</h2>
    <p>Published editions are not silently rewritten. A correction receives a date, the underlying timeline is updated, and the change is recorded in the changelog.</p>
  </article>
  <article class="prose-card">
    <h2>Fan-project boundary</h2>
    <p>{{ site.disclaimer }}</p>
    <p>The institutional field-memo presentation is editorial fiction. It does not represent an actual company, studio, research institute, or production document.</p>
  </article>
</section>
